<br>
When we moved to this server, I started keeping track of people who were sweet to me, and those who were arses. Any time someone does something exceptionally nice or mean to me, I make a note of it, because Ive found Life to be very much like a Dickens novel at times--people you meet when you're young can resurface at the oddest times... <br>
<br>
For instance, two days ago, Poppy and Buran were holding an orc camp in EC the other day when 3 &quot;goods&quot; came over and took it (Poppy was on a CR at the time, but we had broken the spawn well, and Buran was keeping it clear with no trouble). Buran told the newcomers he had the camp just fine, explained Poppy was on her way back, and they didnt care. (At least one of them could understand him, too). They took all of the spawns and the DF belts until Poppy arrived, at which time they left.<br>
<br>
That was two stikes against them in my book: bad RPing AND KSing a camp. Soo... They're on my black list, with the guilds they belonged to noted next to their names.<br>
<br>
I do believe in forgiveness, if its warranted. Everyone makes mistakes and has bad days... And Im not going to hold entire guilds responsible for the actions of one or two members. That being said, Im not going to forget it happened, either. <br>
<br>
In character, Buran believes in the &quot;burn me once, shame on you; burn me twice, shame on me&quot; philosophy. He's good natured, and a fiercely loyal friend, but has limited patience for being messed with. <br>
<br>
Limited patience...and a long memory.<br>
